Objective: To classify iris flower species using K-Nearest Neighbors algorithm.

Algorithm Used: K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
KNN works by finding the nearest data points.

d=\sqrt{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i-y_i)^2}
This is the distance formula KNN uses to find nearest neighbors.

Dataset Used: UCI Machine Learning Repository Iris Dataset
Contains:
* 150 samples
* 4 features
* 3 classes

Steps
1. Load dataset
2. Split into train/test
3. Train KNN model
4. Predict classes
5. Evaluate accuracy
